
[1]entertaining

   ENTERTA'INING, ppr. Receiving with hospitality; receiving and treating
   with provisions and accommodations, for reward; keeping or cherishing
   with favor; engaging the attention; amusing.

   1. Pleasing; amusing; diverting; as an entertaining discourse; an
   entertaining friend.
